Norway Gives Grant to Sri Lanka for Plantations
COLOMBO , September 21 ( Xinhua ) -- The government of Norway has granted Sri Lanka 6.1 million U.S. dollars for the implementation of a Plantation Development Support Program , according to the Sri Lankan Finance Ministry here Monday .
Ministry sources said Norway has been extending this support to Sri Lanka since 1985 for the development of projects in the plantation sector .
The main purpose of the program is to support the creation for plantation communities of settlements with good living and housing conditions .
It also aims to improve the health status and working conditions of the plantation community and labor relations of plantation workers , the sources added .
